  "doc_id": "23823",
  "text": "Zebrafish exhibit strain differences in terms of sensitivity and tolerance to alcohol and are sensitive to pharmacological concentrations of alcohol [CITATION_1] . A proteomic study [CITATION_2] investigated the effects of 4 weeks of chronic alcohol treatment (0.5% (v/v)) on the brain of Danio rerio using a 2D-differential in-gel electrophoresis (2D-DIGE) system combined with MALDIToF MS. The results reported 13 differentially regulated proteins in the supernatant fraction and 18 in the pellet fraction. Voltage-dependent anion channels, heat-shock protein 70 (HSP70), and a-subunit of Go (GNAO1) were upregulated following alcohol exposure. This study reported some novel protein targets as well as substantiated some previously identified alcohol targets.",
